11.Name: unit_monthly_data
11.SqlCommand:
WITH Trailing12Months AS (
    SELECT 
        DATEADD(MONTH, -12, DATEFROMPARTS(YEAR(GETDATE()), MONTH(GETDATE()), 1)) AS StartDate,  -- Start of trailing 12 months
        DATEADD(DAY, -1, DATEADD(MONTH, 1, DATEFROMPARTS(YEAR(GETDATE()), MONTH(GETDATE()), 1))) AS EndDate  -- End of current month
),

MonthSeries AS (
    SELECT 
        DATEPART(YEAR, d.date) AS Year,
        DATEPART(MONTH, d.date) AS Month,
        DATENAME(MONTH, d.date) AS MonthName,  -- Full month name
        DATEFROMPARTS(DATEPART(YEAR, d.date), DATEPART(MONTH, d.date), 1) AS MonthStartDate  -- First day of the month
    FROM 
        rpt.dimdate d
    CROSS JOIN 
        Trailing12Months t12m
    WHERE 
        d.date BETWEEN t12m.StartDate AND t12m.EndDate
    GROUP BY 
        DATEPART(YEAR, d.date), DATEPART(MONTH, d.date), DATENAME(MONTH, d.date), DATEFROMPARTS(DATEPART(YEAR, d.date), DATEPART(MONTH, d.date), 1)
),

AllUnits AS (
    SELECT DISTINCT 
        a.unitFk
    FROM 
        rpt.assessment a
),

MonthUnitCombination AS (
    SELECT 
        ms.Year,
        ms.Month,
        ms.MonthName,
        ms.MonthStartDate,
        au.unitFk
    FROM 
        MonthSeries ms
    CROSS JOIN 
        AllUnits au
),

MonthlyData AS (
    SELECT 
        DATEPART(YEAR, a.date) AS Year,
        DATEPART(MONTH, a.date) AS Month,
        a.unitFk,
        COUNT(CASE 
                  WHEN atv.name = 'Wound Assessment' THEN a.id 
                  ELSE NULL 
              END) AS WoundAssessmentCount,  -- Count of wound assessments
        COUNT(CASE 
                  WHEN atv.assessmentTypeId = 'a4664a75-1e9a-4537-a663-401954f5593d' THEN a.patientFk 
                  ELSE NULL 
              END) AS PatientVisitCount  -- Count of patient visits (non-distinct)
    FROM 
        rpt.assessment a
    INNER JOIN 
        rpt.AssessmentTypeVersion atv
        ON a.assessmentTypeVersionFk = atv.id
    WHERE 
        a.date BETWEEN (SELECT StartDate FROM Trailing12Months) AND (SELECT EndDate FROM Trailing12Months)
    GROUP BY 
        DATEPART(YEAR, a.date), DATEPART(MONTH, a.date), a.unitFk
)

SELECT 
    muc.Year,
    muc.Month,
    muc.MonthName,
    muc.unitFk,
    u.name AS UnitName, -- Unit name from rpt.unit
    ISNULL(md.WoundAssessmentCount, 0) AS 'Wound Assessments',  -- Wound assessment count
    ISNULL(md.PatientVisitCount, 0) AS 'Patient Visits',  -- Patient visit count
    muc.MonthStartDate
FROM 
    MonthUnitCombination muc
LEFT JOIN 
    MonthlyData md
    ON muc.Year = md.Year 
    AND muc.Month = md.Month 
    AND muc.unitFk = md.unitFk
LEFT JOIN 
    rpt.unit u
    ON muc.unitFk = u.id
ORDER BY 
    muc.Year, muc.Month, u.name;

12.Name: wound_assessments_pivot
12.SqlCommand:
WITH Trailing12Months AS (
    SELECT 
        DATEADD(MONTH, -11, DATEFROMPARTS(YEAR(GETDATE()), MONTH(GETDATE()), 1)) AS StartDate,  -- Start of 12 months ago
        DATEADD(DAY, -1, DATEADD(MONTH, 1, DATEFROMPARTS(YEAR(GETDATE()), MONTH(GETDATE()), 1))) AS EndDate  -- End of current month
),
MonthSeries AS (
    SELECT 
        DATEFROMPARTS(DATEPART(YEAR, d.date), DATEPART(MONTH, d.date), 1) AS MonthStartDate  -- First day of the month
    FROM 
        rpt.dimdate d
    CROSS JOIN Trailing12Months t12m
    WHERE 
        d.date BETWEEN t12m.StartDate AND t12m.EndDate
    GROUP BY 
        DATEPART(YEAR, d.date), DATEPART(MONTH, d.date), DATEFROMPARTS(DATEPART(YEAR, d.date), DATEPART(MONTH, d.date), 1)
),
MonthlyData AS (
    SELECT 
        FORMAT(a.date, 'yyyy-MM') AS YearMonth,  -- Combine Year and Month into a single column
        a.unitFk,
        COUNT(DISTINCT a.woundFk) AS WoundCount
    FROM 
        rpt.assessment a
    INNER JOIN 
        rpt.AssessmentTypeVersion atv
        ON a.assessmentTypeVersionFk = atv.id
    WHERE 
        a.date BETWEEN (SELECT StartDate FROM Trailing12Months) AND (SELECT EndDate FROM Trailing12Months)
        AND atv.name = 'Wound Assessment'
    GROUP BY 
        FORMAT(a.date, 'yyyy-MM'), a.unitFk
)
-- Generate the result with 12 rows per unit, for each month in the trailing 12 months
SELECT 
    u.name AS UnitName,
    ms.MonthStartDate AS StartDate,
    FORMAT(ms.MonthStartDate, 'yyyy-MM') AS YearMonth,  -- Combine Year and Month here
    COALESCE(md.WoundCount, 0) AS WoundCount
FROM 
    rpt.unit u
CROSS JOIN 
    MonthSeries ms
LEFT JOIN 
    MonthlyData md 
    ON md.unitFk = u.id AND md.YearMonth = FORMAT(ms.MonthStartDate, 'yyyy-MM')  -- Match on YearMonth
ORDER BY 
    u.name, ms.MonthStartDate;

13.Name: patients_pivot

MonthlyData AS (
    SELECT

    INNER JOIN

    u.name, ms.MonthStartDate;

14.Name: percent_incr_wound
14.SqlCommand:
WITH WoundAssessments AS (
    SELECT 
        a.unitFk,
        DATEPART(YEAR, a.date) AS Year,
        DATEPART(MONTH, a.date) AS Month,
        COUNT(*) AS WoundAssessmentCount
    FROM 
        rpt.assessment a
    INNER JOIN 
        rpt.AssessmentTypeVersion atv
        ON a.assessmentTypeVersionFk = atv.id
    WHERE 
        atv.name = 'Wound Assessment'
        AND a.date BETWEEN DATEADD(MONTH, -9, GETDATE()) AND GETDATE()  -- Last 9 months
    GROUP BY 
        a.unitFk, DATEPART(YEAR, a.date), DATEPART(MONTH, a.date)
),

Prev3Ave AS (
    SELECT 
        wa.unitFk,
        AVG(wa.WoundAssessmentCount * 1.0) AS Prev3Ave  -- Average for the last 3 months
    FROM 
        WoundAssessments wa
    WHERE 
        DATEFROMPARTS(wa.Year, wa.Month, 1) BETWEEN DATEADD(MONTH, -3, GETDATE()) AND GETDATE()  -- Previous 3 months
    GROUP BY 
        wa.unitFk
),

First6MonOf9 AS (
    SELECT 
        wa.unitFk,
        AVG(wa.WoundAssessmentCount * 1.0) AS First6MonOf9  -- Average for the first 6 months of the last 9
    FROM 
        WoundAssessments wa
    WHERE 
        DATEFROMPARTS(wa.Year, wa.Month, 1) BETWEEN DATEADD(MONTH, -9, GETDATE()) AND DATEADD(MONTH, -3, GETDATE())  -- First 6 months of the 9-month period
    GROUP BY 
        wa.unitFk
)

SELECT 
    u.name AS UnitName,  -- Unit name
    ISNULL(p3.Prev3Ave, 0) AS 'Prev 3 Ave',  -- Average for previous 3 months
    ISNULL(f6.First6MonOf9, 0) AS 'First 6 Mon of 9'  -- Average for first 6 months of last 9
FROM 
    rpt.unit u
LEFT JOIN 
    Prev3Ave p3
    ON u.id = p3.unitFk
LEFT JOIN 
    First6MonOf9 f6
    ON u.id = f6.unitFk
ORDER BY 
    u.name;

15.Name: percent_incr_patient
15.SqlCommand:
WITH Trailing12Months AS (
    SELECT 
        DATEADD(MONTH, -12, DATEFROMPARTS(YEAR(GETDATE()), MONTH(GETDATE()), 1)) AS StartDate,  -- Start of trailing 12 months
        DATEADD(DAY, -1, DATEADD(MONTH, 1, DATEFROMPARTS(YEAR(GETDATE()), MONTH(GETDATE()), 1))) AS EndDate  -- End of current month
),

VisitDetails AS (
    SELECT 
        a.unitFk,
        DATEPART(YEAR, a.date) AS Year,
        DATEPART(MONTH, a.date) AS Month,
        COUNT(CASE 
                  WHEN atv.assessmentTypeId = 'a4664a75-1e9a-4537-a663-401954f5593d' THEN a.patientFk 
                  ELSE NULL 
              END) AS PatientVisitCount  -- Total patient visits (not distinct)
    FROM 
        rpt.assessment a
    INNER JOIN 
        rpt.AssessmentTypeVersion atv
        ON a.assessmentTypeVersionFk = atv.id
    WHERE 
        a.date BETWEEN DATEADD(MONTH, -9, GETDATE()) AND GETDATE()  -- Last 9 months
    GROUP BY 
        a.unitFk, DATEPART(YEAR, a.date), DATEPART(MONTH, a.date)
),

Prev3Ave AS (
    SELECT 
        vd.unitFk,
        AVG(vd.PatientVisitCount * 1.0) AS Prev3Ave  -- Average patient visits for last 3 months
    FROM 
        VisitDetails vd
    WHERE 
        DATEFROMPARTS(vd.Year, vd.Month, 1) BETWEEN DATEADD(MONTH, -3, GETDATE()) AND GETDATE()  -- Previous 3 months
    GROUP BY 
        vd.unitFk
),

First6MonOf9 AS (
    SELECT 
        vd.unitFk,
        AVG(vd.PatientVisitCount * 1.0) AS First6MonOf9  -- Average patient visits for first 6 months of last 9
    FROM 
        VisitDetails vd
    WHERE 
        DATEFROMPARTS(vd.Year, vd.Month, 1) BETWEEN DATEADD(MONTH, -9, GETDATE()) AND DATEADD(MONTH, -3, GETDATE())  -- First 6 months of 9-month period
    GROUP BY 
        vd.unitFk
)

SELECT 
    u.name AS unit_name,  -- Unit name
    ISNULL(p3.Prev3Ave, 0) AS 'Prev 3 Ave',  -- Average for previous 3 months
    ISNULL(f6.First6MonOf9, 0) AS 'First 6 Mon of 9'  -- Average for first 6 months of last 9
FROM 
    rpt.unit u
LEFT JOIN 
    Prev3Ave p3
    ON u.id = p3.unitFk
LEFT JOIN 
    First6MonOf9 f6
    ON u.id = f6.unitFk
ORDER BY 
    u.name;

16.Name: wound_assessments_pivot_alltime
16.SqlCommand:
WITH DateRange AS (
    SELECT 
        MIN(a.date) AS MinDate,  -- Earliest assessment date
        GETDATE() AS MaxDate  -- Current date
    FROM 
        rpt.assessment a
),
MonthSeries AS (
    SELECT 
        DATEFROMPARTS(YEAR(d.date), MONTH(d.date), 1) AS MonthStartDate  -- First day of the month
    FROM 
        rpt.dimdate d
    CROSS JOIN DateRange dr
    WHERE 
        d.date BETWEEN dr.MinDate AND dr.MaxDate  -- Generate all months from MinDate to MaxDate
    GROUP BY 
        DATEPART(YEAR, d.date), DATEPART(MONTH, d.date), DATEFROMPARTS(YEAR(d.date), MONTH(d.date), 1)
),
MonthlyData AS (
    SELECT 
        FORMAT(a.date, 'yyyy-MM') AS YearMonth,  -- Combine Year and Month into a single column
        a.unitFk,
        COUNT(DISTINCT a.woundFk) AS WoundCount  -- Count distinct wounds
    FROM 
        rpt.assessment a
    INNER JOIN 
        rpt.AssessmentTypeVersion atv
        ON a.assessmentTypeVersionFk = atv.id
    WHERE 
        atv.name = 'Wound Assessment'  -- Filter for 'Wound Assessment'
    GROUP BY 
        FORMAT(a.date, 'yyyy-MM'), a.unitFk
)
-- Generate the result for all units and all months from the minimum date to the current date
SELECT 
    u.name AS UnitName,
    ms.MonthStartDate AS StartDate,
    FORMAT(ms.MonthStartDate, 'yyyy-MM') AS YearMonth,  -- Combine Year and Month here
    COALESCE(md.WoundCount, 0) AS WoundCount  -- Default to 0 if no data
FROM 
    rpt.unit u
CROSS JOIN 
    MonthSeries ms
LEFT JOIN 
    MonthlyData md 
    ON md.unitFk = u.id AND md.YearMonth = FORMAT(ms.MonthStartDate, 'yyyy-MM')  -- Match on YearMonth
ORDER BY 
    u.name, ms.MonthStartDate;

0.Name: TextElement9
0.Text:
Graph:
This section displays a graphical representation of the trailing 12 months, showing the number of Wound Assessments and Patient Visits conducted each month. At the top of the graph, you can filter the data by unit to focus on specific areas.

Right-Hand Side Indicators:
The indicators on this side compare unit performance over the last 9 months. Each row corresponds to a unit, with the left-most column showing the unit's name. The middle column presents the average performance for the most recent 3 months (up to the current date). The right-most column shows the percentage change when comparing this 3-month average to the performance of the 6 months preceding that period.

Essentially, the 6-month period for comparison starts 9 months ago, and the performance from that period is contrasted with the more recent 3-month average.

The data is broken down into two distinct indicators—Wound Assessments and Patient Visits—each clearly labeled for easy reference.
